Customer segmentation divides customers into groups based on similar characteristics.

K-Means clustering groups data into K clusters by minimizing intra-cluster distance.
The Evaluation Metrics are:

Inertia → Sum of squared distances (lower = better)

Silhouette Score → Measures how well clusters are separated (closer to 1 = better)



Linear Regression predicts student performance based on input features.
It finds a relationship between dependent and independent variables.
The  Evaluation Metrics  are:

R² Score → Accuracy of model (closer to 1 = better)

Mean Squared Error (MSE) → Error (lower = better)
